The paper proposes a new class of locality-sensitive hashing algorithms for similarity search, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the theoretical and empirical analysis of the proposed algorithm, which involves concepts from data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE).
